China allocated 200 million yuan for disaster relief after a devastating earthquake in Sichuan killed over 8,700 people.
The quake, with a magnitude of 7.8, struck densely populated areas, including Chengdu.
Russia's President Dmitry Medvedev offered condolences and assistance to China.
The rain forecasted in Sichuan poses challenges to relief efforts, with risks of landslides.
International support poured in, with Germany and Norway pledging aid.
The death toll may rise as thousands remain buried.
Efforts are underway to aid ethnic minorities affected by the disaster in Wenchuan County, the epicenter of the quake.
